mate_time_window() and assert result equals distance / speed within floating-point tolerance.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Test directly calls the time estimation function with fixed inputs, verifies the formula. No infrastructure, mocking of external systems, or multi-module integration required.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Shift-hours validator rejects routes exceeding remaining shift hours and returns the excess time amount","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"The behavior is a simple comparison: if total_estimated_time > remaining_shift_hours, reject and return excess = total_time - remaining_hours. You can mock time estimation and verify the validation logic directly. No mock-miss: the comparison logic itself is testable in isolation. No infrastructure or module wiring required.","test_description":"Mock time estimation to return fixed values. Test case (a): remaining_shift=3h, route_time=5h → expect rejection with excess=2h. Test case (b): remaining_shift=6h, route_time=5h → expect acceptance. Verify both rejection/acceptance decision and correct excess calculation.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Test mocks one dependency (time estimation) and verifies comparison logic. No multi-module coordination, I/O, or external systems.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.88,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When one address fails geocoding, service skips that address, optimizes remaining N-1 addresses, and reports skipped addresses","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is: does the skip logic correctly integrate with downstream route optimization? Testing skip logic alone (Unit) cannot catch if TSP receives wrong input or if the skip is skipped entirely. You must coordinate the mocked geocoding (injecting 'no results'), the skip decision, and verify that TSP receives N-1 coordinates. MOCK-HIDE risk: if you only test skip in isolation, you miss failures where skip is bypassed in the full pipeline.","test_description":"Provide 5 addresses to the service. Mock the geocoding API to return coordinates for 4 addresses and 'no results' for one specific address. Verify: (a) returned route contains 4 stops, (b) TSP heuristic receives 4 coordinate inputs (not 5), (c) skip report includes the failed address, (d) remaining 4 addresses are optimized correctly.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Test verifies skip logic integrates with TSP—cannot be tested at Unit level. Must confirm skip → TSP receives deduplicated input → route is correct.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Duplicate addresses consolidated into single stop with combined delivery items, not visited twice in route","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The behavior has two parts: (1) duplicates are consolidated with items combined (testable at Unit), and (2) the final route visits each consolidated address exactly once (requires full pipeline). Testing dedup logic alone misses the critical failure: TSP visiting a consolidated address twice due to integration failure. The 'not visited twice' guarantee requires verifying dedup → geocoding → TSP → route output. MOCK-HIDE risk: if you test dedup in isolation, a downstream routing failure (where TSP ignores consolidation) would be invisible.","test_description":"Provide 6 addresses with 3 unique addresses and duplicates (e.g., Address A appears twice with items [1,2] and [3,4], Address B appears twice with items [5] and [6], Address C once with [7]). Mock geocoding. Verify: (a) dedup consolidates to 3 stops with combined items, (b) route visits each unique address exactly once, (c) all items preserved in final route.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Test must verify the complete pipeline (dedup → geocoding → route) to ensure consolidation is respected. Testing dedup alone would not catch routing failures that re-visit consolidated addresses.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13469,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13469},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7296bc96-bcc4-4fb1-88c3-f492e3069314","uuid":"62e13867-33c3-4433-aa71-bc9b4a7ff1f7"}
